b'Position Summary
Astravo is a growing, innovative and customer-centric educational technology company. We seek creative and tenacious individuals to help us drive success through service.

To be successful, you\xe2\x80\x99ll need to be a hands-on initiative taker. We need a broad thinker who can make suggestions, take constructive feedback with a good attitude and without pushback and then go out and personally execute with diligence. We need help scrubbing and formatting data across several sources so it can be used effectively. This isn\xe2\x80\x99t just about manipulating data though. We need someone who can effectively analyze the information and use it to share insights that drive our strategic decision-making. If you like telling stories through data, we\xe2\x80\x99re probably a good fit. You must be comfortable working with large data sets from multiple streams. You\xe2\x80\x99ll be the only person in this role giving you broad responsibility but will have the support of the entire organization.

Candidates must have advanced Microsoft Excel and analytical experience in addition to strong SQL experience. If you are looking for a position to learn and grow your data analysis skills, apply today!

This position is located in our office in Lakewood, CO and is full time, exempt. Open to current Colorado residents only. Relocation assistance is not available.

The salay range is $60,000-$75,000.

Job Duties:
Gather feedback to design, develop, test and implement reports that provide consistent updates to company key performance indicators;
Consistently seek feedback from company staff about their need for information and provide ongoing enhancements to company reports;
Collaborate with executives and organizational leaders to identify 
Proactively ensure quality and accuracy in all reporting throughout the organization;
Develop and maintain data transfer procedures defined through interaction with various company software vendors;
Write custom and ad-hoc SQL queries and queries;
Systematize and automate the migration of data from multiple sources into a standard location that makes aggregation and analysis easy;
Engage with company vendors to understand how data is collected and shared with us and work with them to improve the quality, frequency, consistency, and efficiency of the delivery;
Train company staff and develop documentation to improve awareness of the information available to them and how they can access it to improve their decision-making;
Provide quality assurance of imported data;
Manage and design a reporting environment including data sources and security;
Create predictive modeling to help executives and leaders predict problems, solutions, and outcomes; and
All other duties as assigned.

Essential Knowledge, Skills and Abilities
Excellent communication skills, both written and verbal;
Excellent organizational and analytical skills;
Ability to work in a fast-paced, high energy, team environment and juggle multiple tasks;
Strict attention to detail; and
Achieve daily performance metrics.

Minimum Qualifications
Bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in Business, Computer Science, Information Technologies or related field or equivalent work experience;
Two (2) years report writing/development in a professional environment;
Strong technical background in relational database management, statistics, report development, tools (specifically SQL);
Experience working with data tools such as but not limited to; Excel, Tableau, PowerBI, Looker, Google Data Studio, etc.
Demonstrated experience in handling large data sets and relational databases;
Advanced Microsoft Excel skills; and
Ability to pass required background check.

